**I am trying to find a way to make both types of operations `O(1)`.** My only other idea would be to create another &quot;index&quot; that then tracks only the edges between vertices and then the adjacency list would hold the labels, but that seems quite unnecessarily complex.

If it&#39;s not possible to find a way to make both types of operations `O(1)`, I do want to know what would be the recommended method (out of the two above) of establishing the adjacency list so that the majority of my operations would be `O(1)` when trying to work with data relationships.

I think I would want my operations that &quot;get adjacencies connected by label&quot; to be `O(1)` (i.e. the `adjacencyList` would look like: `(vertexFrom, (label, verticesTo))`) as that would be a good way to filter / retrieve data (by their relationships - AKA label names). But I could be entirely missing the mark and actually it would be better to have the `adjacency list` store by `(vertexFrom, (vertexTo, label))` and if I *need* to check the `label` I would have to loop through each adjacent vertex.

