```
Move above code to root configuration.&lt;br&gt; 
Because beans defined in servlet context is not visible in root/application context as root context is initialized first and then servlet context. 

If you define bean in root context you can use(autowire) it in servlet context. 

#### &lt;sub&gt;**What is mean by root-context and servlet-context**&lt;/sub&gt;
**Root context** ------ *Context&#39;s Loaded by ContextLoaderListener*&lt;br&gt;
**Servlet context** --- *Context&#39;s Loaded by DispatcherServlet*&lt;br&gt;


&lt;sub&gt;If you want to know what is rootContext and what is servletContext and also to have clear idea about accessing beans between context
