answers.body_markdown:
###Answer:
*Unfortunately there is no way of inserting a row/column via the API without specifying a custom batch request body using the `google-spreadsheet` npm package, as it only supports bulk updates for cells and not for other batch requests.*

###Workaround:
You can make a batch request to the API using the `spreadsheets.batchUpdate` method of the `googleapis` library and include an `InsertDimensionRequest` in the resource body.*

###Code:
Firstly you need to build your request:
```lang-js
var req = {
  spreadsheetId: &quot;&lt;spreadsheet-id&gt;&quot;,
  resource: {
    request: [
      {
        spreadsheetId: &quot;&lt;spreadsheet-id&gt;&quot;,
        resource: {
          requests: [
            insertDimension: {
              range: {
                sheetId: 0,
                dimension: &quot;ROWS&quot;,
                startIndex: 1,
                endIndex: 2
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
```
and then send it as the batchUpdate resource body:
```lang-js
function makeRequest() {
  var sheets = google.sheets({ version: &#39;v4&#39;, auth });

  sheets.spreadsheets.batchUpdate({req, function(err, response) {
    if (err) {
      console.error(err);
      return;
    }
    console.log(JSON.stringify(response, null, 2));
  });
}
```

###References:

 - [Google Sheets batchUpdate method](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/spreadsheets.values/batchUpdate)
 - [InsertDimensionRequest update](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/spreadsheets/request#InsertDimensionRequest)
 - [DimensionRange documentation](https://developers.google.com/sheets/api/reference/rest/v4/DimensionRange)

